b'[<p><i><b>UFC Fight Night: Condit vs. Alves</b></i> (also known as <i><b>UFC Fight Night 67</b></i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held on May 30, 2015, at the <a href="/wiki/Goi%C3%A2nia_Arena" title="Goi\xc3\xa2nia Arena">Goi\xc3\xa2nia Arena</a> in <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Goi%C3%A2nia,_Brazil" title="Goi\xc3\xa2nia, Brazil">Goi\xc3\xa2nia, Brazil</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-ConditAlves_2-0"><a href="#cite_note-ConditAlves-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The event was the second that the UFC has hosted in <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Goi%C3%A2nia,_Brazil" title="Goi\xc3\xa2nia, Brazil">Goi\xc3\xa2nia, Brazil</a> after <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Fight_Night:_Belfort_vs._Henderson" title="UFC Fight Night: Belfort vs. Henderson">UFC Fight Night: Belfort vs. Henderson</a> on November 9, 2013.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-ConditAlves_2-1"><a href="#cite_note-ConditAlves-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The event was headlined by a welterweight bout between former <a href="/wiki/List_of_World_Extreme_Cagefighting_champions#Welterweight_Championship" title="List of World Extreme Cagefighting champions">WEC</a> &amp; <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Welterweight_Championship" title="UFC Welterweight Championship">Interim UFC Welterweight champion</a> <a href="/wiki/Carlos_Condit" title="Carlos Condit">Carlos Condit</a> and veteran contender <a href="/wiki/Thiago_Alves_(fighter)" title="Thiago Alves (fighter)">Thiago Alves</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>A welterweight bout between <a href="/wiki/TJ_Waldburger" title="TJ Waldburger">TJ Waldburger</a> and Wendell Oliveira was originally booked for <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Fight_Night_61" title="UFC Fight Night 61">UFC Fight Night 61</a>. However, the bout was cancelled on the day of the weigh-ins, after Waldburger passed out while cutting weight. The pairing had been rescheduled for this event,<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup> but it was scrapped yet again after Waldburger pulled out of the bout on May 19 due to undisclosed reasons.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-6"><a href="#cite_note-6">[6]</a></sup> He was replaced by promotional newcomer <a href="/wiki/Darren_Till" title="Darren Till">Darren Till</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-7"><a href="#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Gilbert_Burns_(fighter)" title="Gilbert Burns (fighter)">Gilbert Burns</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Norman_Parke" title="Norman Parke">Norman Parke</a> at this event. However, Burns was forced to withdraw from the event due to injury and was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Francisco_Trinaldo" title="Francisco Trinaldo">Francisco Trinaldo</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-Burns_out_8-0"><a href="#cite_note-Burns_out-8">[8]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Renato_Moicano" title="Renato Moicano">Renato Moicano</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Mirsad_Bekti%C4%87" title="Mirsad Bekti\xc4\x87">Mirsad Bekti\xc4\x87</a> at the event. However, Moicano pulled out of the fight in late April due to a knee injury and was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Lucas_Martins" title="Lucas Martins">Lucas Martins</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-9"><a href="#cite_note-9">[9]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Jessica_Penne" title="Jessica Penne">Jessica Penne</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Juliana_Lima" title="Juliana Lima">Juliana Lima</a> at the event. However on May 1, Penne was removed from the card and placed into a <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Women%27s_Strawweight_Championship" title="UFC Women\'s Strawweight Championship">UFC Women\'s Strawweight Championship</a> fight against champion <a href="/wiki/Joanna_J%C4%99drzejczyk" title="Joanna J\xc4\x99drzejczyk">Joanna J\xc4\x99drzejczyk</a> on June 20, 2015 at <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Fight_Night_69" title="UFC Fight Night 69">UFC Fight Night 69</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-10"><a href="#cite_note-10">[10]</a></sup> She was replaced by promotional newcomer Ericka Almeida.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-11"><a href="#cite_note-11">[11]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Yan_Cabral" title="Yan Cabral">Yan Cabral</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/K.J._Noons" title="K.J. Noons">K.J. Noons</a> at the event. However on May 19, Cabral pulled out of the fight due to <a href="/wiki/Dengue_fever" title="Dengue fever">dengue fever</a> and was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Alex_Oliveira_(fighter)" title="Alex Oliveira (fighter)">Alex Oliveira</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-12"><a href="#cite_note-12">[12]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>On June 18, it was announced that <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Rony_Jason" title="Rony Jason">Rony Jason</a> tested positive for <a href="/wiki/Hydrochlorothiazide" title="Hydrochlorothiazide">hydrochlorothiazide</a>, which is a banned <a href="/wiki/Diuretic" title="Diuretic">diuretic</a>, therefore his submission victory against <a href="/wiki/Damon_Jackson" title="Damon Jackson">Damon Jackson</a> was overturned and he received a nine-month suspension.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-13"><a href="#cite_note-13">[13]</a></sup> The UFC rescinded Jason\'s $50,000 "Performance of the Night" award.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-AwardTaken_14-0"><a href="#cite_note-AwardTaken-14">[14]</a></sup> Jason requested an analysis of his second sample, which also came positive for the diuretic.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-15"><a href="#cite_note-15">[15]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-17"><a href="#cite_note-17">[16]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following fighters were awarded $50,000 bonuses:<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-18"><a href="#cite_note-18">[17]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><i>*Due to Jason\'s failed drug test, UFC rescinded his $50,000 "Performance of the Night" award. The award will not be reissued to a different fighter on the card.</i><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-AwardTaken_14-1"><a href="#cite_note-AwardTaken-14">[14]</a></sup>\n</p>]'